column5: Is there a number to the border in International Falls that I can call? Wondering about bringing chicken and eggs over the border. Just don't want to take them and waste them if they aren't allowing them in now.
Call Canadian Customs in Fort Francis. The US side won't care what you bring in. In fact they don't check you Canada does.
Just got back from Canada last week. Took in both raw chicken and eggs. No problem. Border guards didn't even ask if we had any poultry, so it must be OK right now

Spent last week in Canada. Border guard asked us about chicken. Told her it was from Indiana, she said Indiana was on the banned list. We investigated before we left and didn't find that to be the case. Didn't argue.
